WEBVTT

00:00,000 --> 00:04,950
Decision Quality Brief

00:05,000 --> 00:09,950
The useful part of this post is practical: it translates actually into operating behavior.

00:10,000 --> 00:14,950
Make the decision rule visible so frontline managers can apply it consistently.

00:15,000 --> 00:19,950
Run a compact loop: signal, decision, action, evidence, then adjust next cycle.

00:20,000 --> 00:24,950
You get better execution not by adding steps, but by tightening decision quality.

00:25,000 --> 00:29,950
Treat this as an experiment: one decision change, one expected outcome, one review date.
